To generate a table of contents (ToC) automatically in a LaTeX document, you can use the `\tableofcontents` command provided by the `book` and `report` document classes. However, to create a more customized and comprehensive ToC that includes chapter, section, and subsection headings along with their page numbers, you may need to explore other packages. One such popular package is the `tocbibind` package that allows you to include bibliography entries in the ToC. Additionally, you can use the `tocloft` package to modify the style and format of the ToC.

Here's an example of how to generate a ToC automatically in LaTeX, including chapter, section, and subsection headings, using the `tocbibind` and `tocloft` packages:

```latex
\documentclass{book}
\usepackage{lipsum} % for dummy text
\usepackage[titles]{tocloft} % for customizing ToC style
\usepackage[nottoc]{tocbibind} % for including bibliography entries in ToC

