\mainline{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}
\end{chessgame}
\end{document}
```

This code generates a chessboard with white pieces on the move, along with its FEN string `rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1`, and the move notation `0. e4`. You can adjust the FEN string and move notation as needed to display any state of the chessboard and its moves.

